<br>
After hitting 39 tonight, and finishing my run from 34-39 in the Thurgadin mines, I feel this wonderful thread needs to be seen again.<br>
<br>
The mines so far have been the best exp I have gotten in a long time.<br>
<br>
My thoughts:<br>
<br>
-Like the previous posts mentioned, park your pet in the center of the back cave on the lowest level, past the third pit.<br>
<br>
-The advice of keeping the ladder cleared could not be more true.  I used <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>eye of zomm</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to scout from where I was medding (near the overturned mine cart) to peer over the rim of the ladder to see if anything had spawned.  Timing the spawns can be done, but I found scouting with the Eye to be easier and far safer.  Also worked to scout the tunnels branching off from the center safe point, namely to observe the Norman spawnpoint, and the backmost 3 spawn cave.<br>
<br>
-I used a focus fire pet exclusively down here, and I had no consistent problems.<br>
<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Not just the spiders are social</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  The goos are social as well.  I repeat, they will help each other.  I do not know when this was modified, as they were helping each other since I had been down there.  So be careful.  Pulling a goo near its kind will bring them both.  The bats and rats will not help each other.<br>
<br>
-I did not have the chance to encounter 3 spiders spawning in the backmost cave, however I did have to endure 3 goos spawning.  They all came.  Alternating Renew with Blaze worked wonders.<br>
<br>
-As a previous post mentioned, use a quicker cast DD to tag runners before they drop into the pit by the ladder.  Once you gather some crystalline silk nets, using the net's effect works as well.  (approx. same casting time as Shock of Flame, which I used as my lower backup)<br>
<br>
-As for runners, please note, that if you pull to the back cave's center, runners will go to the ladder, drop down, and follow the corridor to the end, where they will pop up on the other side, near the water.  It is important you kill runners before they have a chance to do this, especially if the runner is a spider or goo, since if the river 2 spawn contains a goo or spider, they will rush to attack your pet.<br>
<br>
-I am unclear when it was changed, but rats have the rare chance of dropping a Plague Rat Tail.  And while I could find no real use for it, it did sell for about 1 plat and some change.<br>
<br>
Going from 34-39 went quicker than most any other range of levels for me, aside from the earliest newbie ones.  It is truly beautiful experience to be had down here.  I was making approximately 20-50 plat a night, give or take, just from coin drop, and selling gems, the occaisional amulet, and the plague rat tails, with a nice reward chunk for selling the coldain heads.<br>
<br>
I went to Thurgadin because of this very post.  I am glad I did.  The title of the thread is no overstatement.<br>
<br>
