<br>
If you are having problems with getting out of the water, my first question would be... what is your swimming skill?  2nd question, what is your race?<br>
<br>
I've seen human/elf characters swim out of SH with a swimming in the 75-90 range.  For a dwarf or gnome it takes something closer to a 200 swimming to do the same (so I've heard).  It appears that both height, and swimming skill makes getting out of water easier.  Since magicians can't really change their size, I'd suggest swimming practice.<br>
<br>
PS With my gnome, swimming skill of 80 I don't have problems getting out of the water (in Thurg mines).  I still can't get out of water in SH<br>
<br>
PPS if you get stuck swimming somewhere (like SH) stop moving and cast gate.  We can get out withut someone &quot;succor&quot;ng us.  <br>
<br>
<br>
edit: clarification on PS<br>
